@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Windows Tutorial";
}

<div class="jumbotron">
    <p class="lead"> </p>

    <div class="container">

        <div class="row">

            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-12">

                <ul class="list-group">
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        1. You can download the Arduino software <a href="https://www.arduino.cc/en/Main/Software">here</a>. Choose the Windows installer.
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/arduinoSoftware.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        2. Once downloaded, run the installer by either double clicking the icon in your downloads folder. Agree to the licensing terms.
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/License_Agreement.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        3. Click next.
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/Next.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        4. If you wish to change default install location, select one. Otherwise, hit install.
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/Install.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        5. When prompted, select install on the driver install confirmation.
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/Driver_Install.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        6. Once the Arduino software is successfully downloaded go <a href="https://github.com/unwiredben/Rainbowduino-v3">here</a>, and then click “Download ZIP” on the right hand side.
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/rainbowduinoLibrary.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        7. Unpack the arduino library and move it to your install locations libraries folder. Default installation is at C:\Program files\Arduino\libraries. On 64 bit systems this is C:\Program Files(x86)\Arduino\libraries
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/Moving_Library.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        8. Start the arduino program. If prompted by Windows Firewall, allow the program to run on both public and private networks
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/firewall.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        9. Before you run any examples go to: Tools-> the board selected should be Board: Arduino Duemilanove or Diecimila, the processor should be Processor: ATmega328. Also make sure you have the correct port selected. The correct one is usually COM1
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/Changing_Board.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        10. Now, click "Incandescent Designs" in the top left corner (of this page), and then select “Create a new LED Pattern.” 
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/Home_Page.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        11. Once you are to the "Create" form choose whatever pattern and customization you would like to have.
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/Create_Form.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        12. When you are done completing the form click “Create”, and a “.ino” file will be downloaded to your computer (like the example.ino on the bottom). 
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/Created_Windows.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        13. Click open. If prmpoted, select arduino IDE and check always open .ino files with arduino IDE. Click "Ok" when asked to create a folder.
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/Add_To_Folder.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="font-size:18px">
                        14. Plug in your board if it isn’t already plugged in, and then go to sketch -> upload, and wait for your pattern to run! 
                        <p class="list-group-item-text"><img src="~/Images/Select_Upload.png" style="width:100%" /></p>
                    </li>

                </ul>

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

</div>